---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title="Architecture Analysis: Choosing the Right OS & Hardware - LaptopVette" description="A practical guide comparing Chromebook, Windows, and macOS architectures and how to choose based on user needs." path="/guides/architecture-analysis" type="article" />
</head>
<body>

  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="container"><a href="/" class="logo">Laptop<span>Vette</span></a></div>
  </nav>

  <article class="article-container">
    <h1>Architecture Analysis: Chromebook vs Windows vs macOS</h1>
    <p>Choosing the right platform depends on the user's workflows: light web browsing, heavy creative work, gaming, or family/education use. This guide compares the operating systems and hardware decisions that matter.</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Chromebook Strengths</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Lightweight OS with fast boot times and automatic updates.</li>
        <li>Great for web-first workflows and schools that use Google Workspace.</li>
        <li>Generally more affordable and easier for IT management in bulk deployments.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Windows Strengths</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Wide hardware support, best for legacy applications and gaming.</li>
        <li>Flexible configuration for power users, productivity suites, and enterprise needs.</li>
        <li>Consider CPU/GPU balance and cooling for heavier workloads.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>macOS Strengths</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Tight hardware-software integration, excellent battery life on Apple silicon.</li>
        <li>Strong creative software ecosystem and consistent performance for content creation.</li>
        <li>Higher entry price but good longevity and resale value.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Choosing by User Type</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Students & casual users: Chromebooks or entry Windows laptops.</li>
        <li>Professionals & creators: macOS on Apple silicon or powerful Windows workstations.</li>
        <li>Families: prioritize durability, manageability, and battery life.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background-color: #f8fafc; color: #0f172a; line-height: 1.85; }
    .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; }
    
    /* Navigation */
    .navbar { background: #ffffff; border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; }
    .navbar .container { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; height: 70px; }
    .logo { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: #0f172a; text-decoration: none; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
    .logo span { color: #b91c1c; }
    
    /* Article Container */
    .article-container { max-width: 1064px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 40px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 12px; }
    .article-container h1 { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.25; color: #0f172a; }
    .article-container > p { margin-bottom: 1.8em; line-height: 2.0; text-align: justify; }
    .article-container h2 { font-size: 26px; margin: 64px 0 32px 0; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; padding-left: 15px; }
    .article-container section { margin-bottom: 2em; }
    .article-container ul { list-style: disc inside; }
    .article-container li { margin-bottom: 28px; line-height: 2.0; }
  </style>
</body>
</html>
